---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Curriculum Vitae | Riccardo Fracchioni">

  <section class="page-header">
    <p class="section-label">Curriculum Vitae</p>
    <h1>Academic profile</h1>

    <p class="page-intro">
      Philosophy graduate working on artificial intelligence,
      machine learning, scientific understanding, causal modelling,
      and the philosophical implications of large language models.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="cv-layout">

    <aside class="cv-sidebar">

      <section>
        <h2>Research interests</h2>

        <ul class="compact-list">
          <li>Epistemology of machine learning</li>
          <li>Scientific understanding and explanation</li>
          <li>Causal modelling</li>
          <li>Philosophy of climate science</li>
          <li>Linguistic meaning and large language models</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Skills</h2>

        <ul class="compact-list">
          <li>Bayesian-network modelling with Netica</li>
          <li>Artificial neural network building with Python</li>
          <li>Academic writing with LaTeX</li>
          <li>Data visualisation with Flourish and Canva</li>
          <li>Critical thinking</li>
          <li>Flexible organisation</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Languages</h2>

        <ul class="compact-list">
          <li>Italian — first language</li>
          <li>English — C2</li>
          <li>German — A2</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

    </aside>

    <div class="cv-main">

      <section class="cv-section">
        <h2>About me</h2>

        <p>
          I have a strong interest in interdisciplinary forms of knowledge,
          with a particular focus on artificial intelligence and its
          philosophical implications.
        </p>

        <p>
          My approach combines a solid academic background with an openness
          to technological complexity, international digital culture,
          and hybrid, barrier-free knowledge.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="cv-section">
        <h2>Education</h2>

        <article class="cv-entry">
          <div class="cv-date">2020–2024</div>

          <div>
            <h3>B.A. and M.A. in Philosophy</h3>

            <p class="cv-place">
              University of Turin
            </p>

            <p>
              Final grades: 110/110 for the B.A. and 110/110 with distinction
              for the M.A.
            </p>

            <p>
              Coursework with an emphasis on analytic philosophy,
              specifically philosophy of science, formal epistemology,
              and philosophy of language.
            </p>

            <p>
              At the University of Turin, I acquired a strong methodological
              foundation in academic writing and independent research.
            </p>

            <p>
              <strong>Undergraduate dissertation:</strong>
              <em>
                Does Truth Depend on the Mind? Counterfactual Arguments
                on the Existence of Truth in Mindless Possible Worlds
              </em>
            </p>

            <p>
              <strong>Postgraduate dissertation:</strong>
              <em>
                On the Semantic Competence of Large Language Models
              </em>
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="cv-entry">
          <div class="cv-date">2023–2024</div>

          <div>
            <h3>Exchange Semester</h3>

            <p class="cv-place">
              Ludwig Maximilians Universität München
            </p>

            <p>
              GPA: 1.15.
            </p>

            <p>
              Erasmus exchange at a top-ranked institution in philosophy.
              The course
              <em>Philosophy and Theory of Artificial Intelligence</em>,
              taught by Prof. Levin Hornischer, especially shaped my research
              interests and informed my subsequent Master's dissertation.
            </p>

            <p>
              I also gained basic technical skills in building simple neural
              networks and deepened my knowledge of causal modelling through
              related coursework with Prof. Naftali Weinberger.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="cv-entry">
          <div class="cv-date">2019–2020</div>

          <div>
            <h3>First Year B.A. in Philosophy</h3>

            <p class="cv-place">
              Royal Holloway University of London
            </p>

            <p>
              Upper Second Class Honours.
            </p>

            <p>
              I attended a wide range of courses in general philosophy taught
              in English, developed a strong argumentative method, and became
              familiar with analytically oriented writing and research.
            </p>

            <p>
              This year was especially important in developing an early
              preference for international and cooperative academic
              environments.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section class="cv-section">
        <h2>Other qualifications</h2>

        <article class="cv-entry">
          <div class="cv-date">2025</div>

          <div>
            <h3>Introduction to Machine Learning</h3>

            <p class="cv-place">
              Tech Academy ProfessionAI
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="cv-entry">
          <div class="cv-date">2024</div>

          <div>
            <h3>Python Programming</h3>

            <p class="cv-place">
              Tech Academy ProfessionAI
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section class="cv-section">
        <h2>Academic references</h2>

        <article class="reference-entry">
          <h3>Fabrizio Calzavarini</h3>
          <p>
            <a href="mailto:fabrizio.calzavarini@unito.it">
              fabrizio.calzavarini@unito.it
            </a>
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="reference-entry">
          <h3>Eugenio Petrovich</h3>
          <p>
            <a href="mailto:eugenio.petrovich@unito.it">
